    <item>
      <title>Testing Mastodon Author Tags</title>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Nov 2024 22:05:15 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://crazymilk.net/blog/testing-mastodon-author-tags.html</guid>
      <link>https://crazymilk.net/blog/testing-mastodon-author-tags.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[
          <p>... by writing a short post about testing Mastodon author tags. It's all very <code>meta</code>. Quite literally because you add a <code>meta</code> tag with the <code>fediverse:creator</code> property to your HTML document's <code>head</code>.</p>
          <p>(Hat tip to David Chartier for <a href="https://toot.cafe/@chartier/113516479426771675">pointing me</a> to <a href="https://rknight.me/blog/setting-up-mastodon-author-tags/">Robb Knight's instructions</a>.)</p>
      ]]></description>
    </item>

