    <item>
      <title>It's Grittibänz Season Already</title>
      <pubDate>Thu, 14 Nov 2024 07:18:18 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://crazymilk.net/blog/grittibaenz-season-already.html</guid>
      <link>https://crazymilk.net/blog/grittibaenz-season-already.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[
        <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/grittibaenz-season-already.webp" alt="A tray holding a cup of coffee, a glass of water, and a tasty-looking bread man" width=960 height=784 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        <p>I was feeling a bit down this afternoon, so I decided to walk out to a local cafe for a cup of coffee and maybe a sweet treat. To my surprise it's already Grittibänz season. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stutenkerl">Grittibänz</a> are bread men made from sweet dough. They are traditional in December around Saint Nicholas Day (<a href="https://www.helvetickitchen.com/recipes/2017/12/4/grittibanz">Recipe</a>).</p>
        <p>It seems like the internet (and perhaps real life) is full of bad stuff lately. Be kind to yourself and don't forget to give yourself a little treat every now and then.</p>
      ]]></description>
    </item>

