    <item>
      <title>Just a Little Bit of Mist</title>
      <pubDate>Wed, 28 Aug 2024 09:28:48 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://crazymilk.net/blog/just-a-little-bit-of-mist.html</guid>
      <link>https://crazymilk.net/blog/just-a-little-bit-of-mist.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[
      <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/just-a-little-bit-of-mist.webp" alt="Early morning view of a lake with a light mist rising from the water. Forested hills still in shadow lie in the background. The sky is blue with a few low clouds." width=960 height=540 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
      <p>... over Lake Ägeri this morning. The mist forms occasionally when the water is warmer than the air (a necessary but not sufficient condition). Today was my third day in a row of waking up early and getting a quick 30-minute paddle in before work, but it was the first day with some <a href="https://www.meteoswiss.admin.ch/weather/weather-and-climate-from-a-to-z/fog/fog-smoking-lakes.html">evaporation fog</a> despite the other two days being colder.</p>
      ]]></description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>Fresh Eggs</title>
      <pubDate>Mon, 12 Aug 2024 10:56:07 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://crazymilk.net/blog/fresh-eggs.html</guid>
      <link>https://crazymilk.net/blog/fresh-eggs.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[
      <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/fresh-eggs.webp" alt="A brown hen in a chicken coop." width=960 height=960 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
      <p>Living outside of the big city in Switzerland means living near farms, mostly small ones. I live near three small farms. They all sell their products in small honor system stores. For the farm next door I pick up eggs directly from the coop. They're actually cheaper than grocery store eggs, and I know the chickens are treated well because I can see them pecking in their yard from our apartment. Anyway I picked up fresh eggs on Saturday and was just reflecting on how different this is for me than life in the suburbs in the United States.</p>
      ]]></description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>Fuorcla Surlej</title>
      <pubDate>Sun, 4 Aug 2024 13:58:53 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://crazymilk.net/blog/fuorcla-surlej.html</guid>
      <link>https://crazymilk.net/blog/fuorcla-surlej.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[
        <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/fuorcla-surlej.webp" alt="Panorama view of high mountains, some of them with glaciers. Rocks and short green grass are in the foreground. The sky is blue with multiple puffy white clouds." width=960 height=266 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        <p>We've been here <a href="https://mpospese.com/2023/07/10/fuorcla-surlej/">before</a>, but the Fuorcla Surlej is always worth another visit if you're in the area. It's a short out-and-back hike from the Corvatsch cable car's Murtèl middle station, but the relatively high altitude (2,755m) always keeps the walk interesting for me: 4.59 km, 143m ascent, 1h8m, 11°C ⛅️.</p>
        <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/fuorcla-surlej-2.webp" alt="View of high mountains, some of them with glaciers. Rocks and short green grass are in the foreground. The sky is blue with multiple puffy white clouds." width=960 height=540 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/fuorcla-surlej-3.webp" alt="Tiny pink alpine flowers set against brown dirt and light gray stones." width=960 height=960 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/fuorcla-surlej-4.webp" alt="Tiny blue alpine flowers growing next to a thistle growing from a pile of gray stones." width=960 height=960 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
      ]]></description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>Muottas Muragl</title>
      <pubDate>Sat, 3 Aug 2024 19:39:52 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://crazymilk.net/blog/muottas-muragl.html</guid>
      <link>https://crazymilk.net/blog/muottas-muragl.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[
      <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/muottas-muragl.webp" alt="Panorama of high alpine terrain with a small blue green lake on the left, dark gray craggy mountains dotted with a bit of old snow in the distance, and green heather dotted with white stone in the foreground." width=960 height=392 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
      <p>This weekend we are visiting Sils Maria in the Engadin region of eastern Switzerland. Today I hiked from the funicular station of Muottas Muragl to Lej (Lake) Muragl: 7.76km, 397m ascent, 2h45m, 15°C ⛅️. It was a lovely hike that reached a maximum altitude of 2,750m. I saw cows, horses, and a marmot (and many fellow hikers).</p>
      <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/muottas-muragl-2.webp" alt="View of high alpine valley with mountains in the distance. The foreground is low green vegetation mixed with stones and speckled with small yellow flowers." width=960 height=720 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
      <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/muottas-muragl-3.webp" alt="Closeup of some small intensely blue alpine flowers growing in between stones." width=960 height=960 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
      <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/muottas-muragl-4.webp" alt="View of high alpine valley clearly left behind by a glacier. The sides are green but the bottom and upper end are dark gray scree." width=960 height=720 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
      ]]></description>
    </item>

